{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:psalms.80",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 80,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 80 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:1",
      "text": "Unto the end, for the winepresses, a psalm for Asaph himself.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:2",
      "text": "Rejoice to God our helper: sing aloud to the God of Jacob.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:3",
      "text": "Take a psalm, and bring hither the timbrel: the pleasant psaltery with the harp.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:4",
      "text": "Blow up the trumpet on the new moon, on the noted day of your solemnity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:5",
      "text": "For it is a commandment in Israel, and a judgment to the God of Jacob.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:6",
      "text": "He ordained it for a testimony in Joseph, when he came out of the land of Egypt: he heard a tongue which he knew not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:7",
      "text": "He removed his back from the burdens: his hands had served in baskets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:8",
      "text": "Thou calledst upon me in affliction, and I delivered thee: I heard thee in the secret place of tempest: I proved thee at the waters of contradiction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:9",
      "text": "Hear, O my people, and I will testify to thee: O Israel, if thou wilt hearken to me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:10",
      "text": "there shall be no new god in thee: neither shalt thou adore a strange god.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:11",
      "text": "For I am the Lord thy God, who brought thee out of the land of Egypt: open thy mouth wide, and I will fill it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:12",
      "text": "But my people heard not my voice: and Israel hearkened not to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:13",
      "text": "So I let them go according to the desires of their heart: they shall walk in their own inventions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:14",
      "text": "If my people had heard me: if Israel had walked in my ways:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:15",
      "text": "I should soon have humbled their enemies, and laid my hand on them that troubled them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:16",
      "text": "The enemies of the Lord have lied to him: and their time shall be for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:psalms.80.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:17",
      "text": "And he fed them with the fat of wheat, and filled them with honey out of the rock.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
